\pagenumbering{arabic}

\chapter{Introduction}
Brief details introducing the topic of your \textit{project work}. Here  you  need  to  outline  the  underlying  concepts and   a 
brief version of any theory needed to discuss the project (if required).
\chapter{Literature Survey}
Literature Survey is the process of reading, analyzing, evaluating, and summarizing scholarly materials about a specific topic/area. When you write a literature review in respect of your project, you have to write about researches made by various analysts - their methodology and the conclusions they have arrived at. You should also give an account of how this research has influenced your work. All sources \cite{bib1} cited in the literature review should be listed in the references.
\chapter{Problem Definition}
A problem statement is a concise description of the issues that need to be addressed by the project group. This statement should illustrate a clear vision and the overall method that will be used to solve the problem at hand.

\chapter{Methodology}
The work that you have done so far related with the project should be stated  clearly. Include separate sections for details of design, implementation etc.
\begin{figure}[!b]
\centering
  \includegraphics[scale = 0.3]{sample.png}
  \caption{Image caption}
  \label{label1}
\end{figure}

\chapter{Results}

Show the results of your project by suitable test cases/data sets. Give the analysis of the result obtained (or the proof of currectness of the algorithm) by comparing results with that of any alternative system/algorithm.

\chapter{Conclusion and Future work}

Give a brief description of the work that you have done and mention the overall results and findings. Suggest modifications/extentions possible over your project if any.

